description:
Similar to CDRIVER-2789, I observed that CNAME records could be returned by res_nsearch. I discovered this by accident when testing SRV polling but forgetting to override my DNS. Connecting to this URI:

{noformat}
mongodb+srv://server.mongodb.com/?tls=true&tlsinsecure=true&heartbeatFrequencyMS=1000&directConnection=false
{noformat}

Will attempt to do SRV and TXT lookup on {{_mongodb._tcp.server.mongodb.com}}. This gave a strange error, looking like it was applying malformed text to the URI's options. When debugging it seems that the CNAME records returned were being applied as SRV / TXT records. Even querying with {{dig}} shows that CNAME records are returned when SRV / TXT is requested:
{code}
$ dig -t txt _mongodb._tcp.server.mongodb.com
...
;; ANSWER SECTION:
_mongodb._tcp.server.mongodb.com. 3600 IN CNAME	glb.mongodb.com.
...
{code}

This may be a misconfigured DNS server, but we should handle that gracefully. Let's apply the same fix of CDRIVER-2789 to the libresolv implementation of seedlist discovery and filter out non matching records.

Crud tests are skipped if libmongoc is not built with sessions support:
https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/1.16.0/src/libmongoc/tests/test-mongoc-crud.c/#L40-L43
{code}
   install_json_test_suite_with_check (suite,
                                       resolved,
                                       &test_crud_cb,
                                       test_framework_skip_if_no_sessions);
{code}

But I do not believe this should require driver sessions support. However, changing this to:
{code}
   install_json_test_suite_with_check (suite,
                                       resolved,
                                       &test_crud_cb,
                                       TestSuite_CheckLive);
{code}

Does result in some test failures:
https://evergreen.mongodb.com/version/5e418a2232f4174d3be1b9c3

Which I cannot reproduce locally on my macOS machine.

A mongoc_buffer_t is a small struct with a data pointer, data length, capacity, and reallocation function.

Originally, it also had an offset field, which was removed in this commit: CDRIVER-2266

A side-effect of that is there are three lines like:
{code}
memmove (&buffer->data[0], buffer->data, buffer->len);
{code}

Which are effectively no-ops.

One case was removed in https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/commit/26137b5c0883bd0705833c0ec9212694d9c88650 but three still remain.

